ring fence
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a fence that surrounds an area of land for a specific purpose or a boundary fence.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka ring-fence
Citations
